    {
      "id": "Hk9huUSkV1SGWOnTghphP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 7423.104072735543,
      "y": 777.2608058753792,
      "width": 1114.19921875,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4C",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1389142339,
      "version": 823,
      "versionNonce": 1189265667,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1765047649359,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "user disconnection\n\nWhen a user disconnects from the internet, the persistent connection between the client and server is lost\na naive way to handle userdisconnection is to mark the user  as offline each and toggle it when the\nconnection re-stablishes but updating status on every disconnect/reconnect would make the \npresence indicator to cahnge too often\n\nWe introduce a heartbeat mechanism to solve this problem. Periodically, an online client sends a heartbeat even to\npresence servers. if presence servers receive a heartbet within a certain time, say x seconds from the clietn,\na user is consider online. Otherwise is offilne",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "user disconnection\n\nWhen a user disconnects from the internet, the persistent connection between the client and server is lost\na naive way to handle userdisconnection is to mark the user  as offline each and toggle it when the\nconnection re-stablishes but updating status on every disconnect/reconnect would make the \npresence indicator to cahnge too often\n\nWe introduce a heartbeat mechanism to solve this problem. Periodically, an online client sends a heartbeat even to\npresence servers. if presence servers receive a heartbet within a certain time, say x seconds from the clietn,\na user is consider online. Otherwise is offilne",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
